          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A sample consisting of three layers of metal films",
                "for cross section measurement was made by means of a",
                "DC magnetron sputtering method. A layer of ~5 nm",
                "tantalum film was first sputtered on a piece of 7 mu-m",
                "Al foil substrate, which was taken as the internal ion",
                "dose reference, and a layer of titanium film with",
                "~50 nm thickness was deposited onto the Ta film",
                "subsequently as the deuterium storage layer, and then",
                "about 5 nm nickel was deposited onto the Ti film as",
                "the anti-oxidation layer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The scattered protons were detected at two",
                "angles in laboratory frame, 155. and 165. degr.,",
                "respectively, and the Au/Si surface barrier detector",
                "was put on a movable frame, which could be shifted",
                "along a circle orbit, so that the detection angle",
                "can be changed in the experiment process."
              ]
            }
          ],
